<paragraph blockId="258.[151,1436,1596,1777]" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis box="[207,450,1674,1698]" italics="true" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: The broad, parallel-sided anal point, together with the long, pointed median volsella and the sharply pointed inferior volsella with rounded accessory lobe separate the male imago from other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="258.[151,1436,1830,2010]" box="[151,363,1830,1854]" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis box="[151,282,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">Male imago</emphasis>
(n = 1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="258.[151,1436,1830,2010]" box="[151,914,1869,1893]" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">
Total length 
<quantity box="[289,390,1869,1893]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.11" pageId="258" pageNumber="259" unit="mm" value="3.11">3.11 mm</quantity>
. Wing length not measurable. Coloration brown
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="258.[151,1436,1830,2010]" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[285,395,1908,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 98" captionStartId="259.[151,250,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[323,1302,397,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-122@259.[226,1360,372,1884]" captionTargetPageId="259" captionText="FIGURE 98. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A–D. P. laticauda sp. n., male. A—head; B—cibarial pump and stipes; C—apex of wing; D—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect.; E—virga. F–K. P. longicornia sp. n., male. F—head; G—wing; H—third palpomere; I—cibarial pump and stipes; J—hypopygium. left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect; K—virga." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288609/files/figure.png" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">Fig. 98 A</figureCitation>
). Antenna lost. Temporal setae 5, consisting of 2 inner verticals and 3 outer verticals. Clypeus with 4 setae. Tentorium 96 µm long, 23 µm wide. Cibarial pump and stipes as in 
<figureCitation box="[1036,1141,1947,1971]" captionStart="FIGURE 98" captionStartId="259.[151,250,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[323,1302,397,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-122@259.[226,1360,372,1884]" captionTargetPageId="259" captionText="FIGURE 98. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A–D. P. laticauda sp. n., male. A—head; B—cibarial pump and stipes; C—apex of wing; D—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect.; E—virga. F–K. P. longicornia sp. n., male. F—head; G—wing; H—third palpomere; I—cibarial pump and stipes; J—hypopygium. left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect; K—virga." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288609/files/figure.png" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">Fig. 98 B</figureCitation>
. Stipes 87 µm long, 34 µm wide. Lengths of first three palpomeres (in µm): 21, 30, 69, apical palpomeres lost, third palpomere as in 
<figureCitation box="[1295,1413,1986,2010]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="282.[151,250,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[239,1352,437,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-141@282.[226,1360,404,1916]" captionTargetPageId="282" captionText="FIGURE 109. Pseudosmittia spp., male hypopygia. A–C. P. roquei Andersen, Saether et Mendes; A—hypopygium, dorsal view; B—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right; C— gonostylus. D–G. P. cambuciensis Andersen, Saether et Mendes. D—hypopygium, dorsal view; E—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right; F—median volsella, dorsal view; G— gonostylus. (From Andersen et al., 2010.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288653/files/figure.png" pageId="258" pageNumber="259">Fig. 109 C</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="259.[151,1436,158,308]" box="[211,1419,158,182]" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">Thorax. Antepronotum with 4 lateral setae. Dorsocentrals 11, acrostichals 2, prealars 4. Scutellum with 6 setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="259.[151,1436,158,308]" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[289,399,197,221]" captionStart="FIGURE 98" captionStartId="259.[151,250,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[323,1302,397,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-122@259.[226,1360,372,1884]" captionTargetPageId="259" captionText="FIGURE 98. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A–D. P. laticauda sp. n., male. A—head; B—cibarial pump and stipes; C—apex of wing; D—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect.; E—virga. F–K. P. longicornia sp. n., male. F—head; G—wing; H—third palpomere; I—cibarial pump and stipes; J—hypopygium. left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect; K—virga." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288609/files/figure.png" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">Fig. 98 C</figureCitation>
). Only one wing present. Costal extension 34 µm long. R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1049,1072,212,226]" fontSize="6" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">4+5</subScript>
ending slightly distal to apex of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[175,199,255,269]" fontSize="6" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">3+4</subScript>
; Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[245,253,255,269]" fontSize="6" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">1</subScript>
slightly curved. R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[452,476,255,269]" fontSize="6" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">4+5</subScript>
without setae, other veins not clear.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="259.[151,1436,158,308]" box="[211,320,284,308]" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">Legs.Lost</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288609" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5288609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288609/files/figure.png" pageId="259" pageNumber="260" startId="259.[151,250,1905,1928]" targetBox="[323,1302,397,1845]" targetPageId="259">
<paragraph blockId="259.[151,1436,1905,1989]" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1905,1928]" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">FIGURE 98</emphasis>
. 
