<taxonomicNameLabel box="[763,822,1906,1927]" pageId="259" pageNumber="260" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male. A—head; B—cibarial pump and stipes; C—apex of wing; D—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect.; E—virga. F–K. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferrington Jr &amp; Saether, 2011" authorityName="Ferrington Jr &amp; Saether" authorityYear="2011" box="[956,1098,1936,1958]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudosmittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="259" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornia" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[956,1098,1936,1958]" italics="true" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">P. longicornia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1104,1161,1937,1958]" pageId="259" pageNumber="260">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1104,1161,1937,1958]" pageId="259" pageNumber="260" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male. F—head; G—wing; H—third palpomere; I—cibarial pump and stipes; J—hypopygium. left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect; K—virga.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="260.[151,1437,158,338]" pageId="260" pageNumber="261">
Hypopygium (
<figureCitation box="[370,476,158,182]" captionStart="FIGURE 98" captionStartId="259.[151,250,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[323,1302,397,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-122@259.[226,1360,372,1884]" captionTargetPageId="259" captionText="FIGURE 98. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A–D. P. laticauda sp. n., male. A—head; B—cibarial pump and stipes; C—apex of wing; D—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect.; E—virga. F–K. P. longicornia sp. n., male. F—head; G—wing; H—third palpomere; I—cibarial pump and stipes; J—hypopygium. left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect; K—virga." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288609/files/figure.png" pageId="260" pageNumber="261">Fig. 98 D</figureCitation>
). Anal point 37 µm long, 14 µm wide medially, completely free of microtrichia, but with a few lateral setae. Tergite IX with 10 setae, laterosternite IX with 5 setae. Transverse sternapodeme 50 µm long, no oral projections. Virga (
<figureCitation box="[416,523,236,260]" captionStart="FIGURE 98" captionStartId="259.[151,250,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[323,1302,397,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-122@259.[226,1360,372,1884]" captionTargetPageId="259" captionText="FIGURE 98. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A–D. P. laticauda sp. n., male. A—head; B—cibarial pump and stipes; C—apex of wing; D—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect.; E—virga. F–K. P. longicornia sp. n., male. F—head; G—wing; H—third palpomere; I—cibarial pump and stipes; J—hypopygium. left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect; K—virga." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288609/files/figure.png" pageId="260" pageNumber="261">Fig. 98 E</figureCitation>
) 11 (?) µm long. Gonocoxite 144 µm long; superior volsella 23 µm long, median volsella 41 µm long, inferior volsella 25 µm long. Gonostylus 71 µm long, with dense microtrichia on inner margin; megaseta 9 µm long. HR 2.05, HV 3.12.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="260.[151,413,392,455]" box="[151,413,392,416]" pageId="260" pageNumber="261">
